  "description": [
    "w i I v 5 V 1 A i Civil Rights Tie In With Labor Law Sought In Senate WASHINGTON Feb 28 A NPA proposal totie in civil rights a clause to the ifew labor legislation which would prevent labor unions from barring work ers because of race or religion was injected into the senate labor com mittee hearing last Wednesday The proposal was advanced by Edgar G Brown director of the National Negro council and Elmer W Henderson head of the Ameri can Council on Human rights Both Brown and Henderson ap pealed for the inclusion of the clause but did not concur alto gether with each others views Brown testified that 17 AFL un ions require their members to be white but that William Green AFL president had told him he had no objection to the proposed amendment However Brown said a fair employment practice commission provision should also be written in the new labor legislation Hen derson objected to this as did Sen Hubert Humphrey D Minn who was largely responsi ble for drafting the civil rights plank in the 1948 Democratic platform Outright opposition to the in clusion of a civil rights provision in the measure"
  ],
